# Iconography & FontAwesome

## 1. Script Integration
- **Source:** Use the personal FontAwesome Kit: `https://kit.fontawesome.com/a21f98a3f6.js`.
- **Placement:** Must be loaded in the `<head>` of `index.html` with the `crossorigin="anonymous"` attribute.
- **Loading:** Use `async` or `defer` to not block loading of website.

## 2. Usage Patterns
- **Library:** Use "Pro" or "Free" icons consistent with the kit's availability (prefer `fas` for solid, `far` for regular).
- **Sizing:** - **Header Icons:** `1.2rem` (approx 20px).
    - **Bottom Nav Icons:** `1.5rem` (approx 24px) to ensure thumb-readability.
    - **Notifications:** Use the `fa-layers` pattern for numeric badges.

## 3. Component Mapping
- **Navigation:**
    - Home: `<i class="fa-solid fa-house"></i>`
    - Notifications: `<i class="fa-solid fa-bell"></i>`
    - Menu/Hamburger: `<i class="fa-solid fa-bars"></i>`
    - User/Profile: `<i class="fa-solid fa-circle-user"></i>`
- **Actions:**
    - Close/Dismiss: `<i class="fa-solid fa-xmark"></i>`
    - Chevron/Dropdown: `<i class="fa-solid fa-chevron-down"></i>`

## 4. Accessibility & CSS
- **Aria:** Every icon must include `aria-hidden="true"` if it is purely decorative.
- **Coloring:** Icons should inherit `currentColor` from their parent elements (e.g., the `.active` class in the Bottom Nav).
- **Alignment:** Use `display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;` for containers to prevent "jumping" text.

## 5. Blueprint Implementation (HTML)
```html
<script src="[https://kit.fontawesome.com/a21f98a3f6.js](https://kit.fontawesome.com/a21f98a3f6.js)" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

<button class="icon-btn" aria-label="Open Menu">
  <i class="fa-solid fa-bars" aria-hidden="true"></i>
</button>